"title": "5449: poverty, remedies for",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5449: poverty, remedies for",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although poverty can never be totally eliminated from this sinful world, it can be alleviated. Scripture provides guidance concerning how this may be done.</p>\n<h2>Poverty will always exist in this world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:11\">MAT 26:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:8\">JHN 12:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:11\">DEU 15:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's concern over poverty</h2>\n<h3>God cares for the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:10\">PSA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:10\">PSA 68:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:4-Deut15:5\">DEU 15:4–15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:16\">JOB 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:6\">PSA 14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps113:7\">PSA 113:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:12\">PSA 140:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:4\">ISA 25:4</a></p>\n<h3>The law made concessions for poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:7\">LEV 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:11\">LEV 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:8\">LEV 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:21-Lev14:22\">LEV 14:21–14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:8\">LEV 27:8</a></p>\n<h3>God judges those who oppress the poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:12-Ezek18:13\">EZK 18:12–18:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:1-Amos4:2\">AMO 4:1–4:2</a></p>\n<h2>The poor should be encouraged to help themselves</h2>\n<h3>Mosaic law enabled the poor to help themselves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:11\">EXO 23:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:10\">LEV 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:22\">LEV 23:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:25\">LEV 25:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:28\">LEV 25:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39\">LEV 25:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:41\">LEV 25:41</a> <em>The jubilee helped towards release from the poverty trap</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:25\">DEU 23:25</a></p>\n<h3>Paul exhorts the poor to work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:11\">1TH 4:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:10\">2TH 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Paul sets the poor an example</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:34\">ACT 20:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:9\">1TH 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:8\">2TH 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>The relatives of the poor should help</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:4\">1TI 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:9-Gen45:11\">GEN 45:9–45:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:25\">LEV 25:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:8\">1TI 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:16\">1TI 5:16</a></p>\n<h2>Those better off should help the poor</h2>\n<h3>The poor can be helped by means of gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:4\">ACT 10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:7-Deut15:8\">DEU 15:7–15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:9\">PSA 112:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:20\">PRO 31:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:36\">ACT 9:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:28\">EPH 4:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17-1Tim6:18\">1TI 6:17–6:18</a></p>\n<h3>The poor can be helped in practical ways</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34-Matt25:40\">MAT 25:34–25:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:41\">LUK 11:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:13\">LUK 14:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:36\">ACT 9:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:39\">ACT 9:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:9-1Tim5:10\">1TI 5:9–5:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:15-Jas2:16\">JAS 2:15–2:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:17\">1JN 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>The poor can be helped by others upholding justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:3\">PSA 82:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:12-Deut24:15\">DEU 24:12–24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:22\">PRO 22:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:7\">PRO 29:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:14\">PRO 29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:9\">PRO 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:2\">ISA 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:16\">JER 22:16</a></p>\n<h2>The church should help the poor</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:10\">GAL 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:17\">ACT 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:26\">ROM 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:16\">1TI 5:16</a></p>\n<h2>God's greatest gift to the poor is the good news of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:5\">MAT 11:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:21\">LUK 14:21</a> <em>Scripture regards spiritual and social welfare as closely connected.</em></p>",
